During a visit to Emintsimadze Palace in Cape Coast, Ghana, the Vice President expresses gratitude for the warm welcome and appoints the Ambassador to Ghana as an official liaison. She acknowledges the importance of trust, consistency, and reciprocity in building good relationships. The Vice President also emphasizes the significance of remembering history and learning from it to shape our future. She expresses optimism about Ghana's prioritization of education and its potential to create global connections and interdependence. The Vice President expresses her honor to be in Ghana and looks forward to future interactions.